<subSubSection id="E9AF48D2BF4BFF8B1D95F9FA99E5F8D0" pageId="22" pageNumber="273" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="A10A1B59BF4BFF8B1D95F9FA99E5F8D0" blockId="22.[151,1437,151,2013]" pageId="22" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF4BFF8B1D95F9FA99F8F906" bold="true" box="[199,462,1662,1688]" pageId="22" pageNumber="273">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
Based on the presence of six dorsal striae and a submarginal stria on each elytron, the new species can be classified within 
<taxonomicName id="66B560DABF4BFF8B1F13F9279ACBF922" authorityName="Regimbart" authorityYear="1899" box="[577,765,1699,1725]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Copelatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="irinus">
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF4BFF8B1F13F9279ACBF922" box="[577,765,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="273">Copelatus irinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group. Elongate habitus, complete elytral striation and male median lobe without distinct process place 
<taxonomicName id="66B560DABF4BFF8B1E5AF9439BECF97F" authority="Jiang &amp; Zhao &amp; Yang &amp; Jia &amp; Hájek, 2022" authorityName="Jiang &amp; Zhao &amp; Yang &amp; Jia &amp; Hájek" authorityYear="2022" box="[776,986,1735,1761]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Copelatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tengchongensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF4BFF8B1E5AF9439BECF97F" box="[776,986,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="273">C. tengchongensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="88F27A30BF4BFF8B1EB7F9439C76F97F" box="[997,1088,1735,1761]" pageId="22" pageNumber="273" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in the 
<taxonomicName id="66B560DABF4BFF8B19CAF9439D1CF97E" authorityName="Sharp" authorityYear="1884" box="[1176,1322,1735,1761]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Copelatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF4BFF8B19CAF9439D1CF97E" box="[1176,1322,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="273">C. japonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex. Within the complex, the new species can be undoubtedly recognised only based on the shape of male genitalia: 
<taxonomicName id="66B560DABF4BFF8B18D1F96F9972F8B7" authority="Jiang &amp; Zhao &amp; Yang &amp; Jia &amp; Hájek, 2022" authorityName="Jiang &amp; Zhao &amp; Yang &amp; Jia &amp; Hájek" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Copelatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tengchongensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF4BFF8B18D1F96F9972F8B7" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="273">C. tengchongensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="88F27A30BF4BFF8B1C19F88B9995F8B7" box="[331,419,1807,1833]" pageId="22" pageNumber="273" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is characteristic with the median lobe broadest in midpart and the apical part only slightly narrowing to apex (
<figureCitation id="398E07DCBF4BFF8B1C20F8B799F0F8D0" box="[370,454,1843,1870]" captionStart="FIGURES 63–70" captionStartId="41.[151,264,1403,1427]" captionTargetBox="[216,1366,200,1362]" captionTargetId="figure-18@41.[205,1383,181,1379]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURES 63–70. Male genitalia of Copelatus. 63, 65, 67, 69. median lobe in lateral view; 64, 66, 68, 70. paramere. 63–64. C. tengchongensis sp. nov. (holotype, Beihai, Yunnan); 65–66. C. weymarni (Honshu, Japan); 67–68. C. xiniudong sp. nov. (holotype, Xiniudong, Guizhou); 69–70. C. zimmermanni (Danxiashan, Guangdong). Scale bar 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6410764" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6410764/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="273">Fig. 63</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E9AF48D2BF4BFF8B1D95F8D39CB4F80B" pageId="22" pageNumber="273" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="A10A1B59BF4BFF8B1D95F8D39CB4F80B" blockId="22.[151,1437,151,2013]" pageId="22" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF4BFF8B1D95F8D39978F8EF" bold="true" box="[199,334,1879,1905]" pageId="22" pageNumber="273">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species is named after its area of occurrence – Tengchong County, where both known localities of the species lie. The specific epithet is an adjective in the nominative singular.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E9AF48D2BF4BFF8B1D95F81A9ABBF843" pageId="22" pageNumber="273" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="A10A1B59BF4BFF8B1D95F81A9ABBF843" blockId="22.[151,1437,151,2013]" pageId="22" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF4BFF8B1D95F81A9957F826" bold="true" box="[199,353,1950,1976]" pageId="22" pageNumber="273">Distribution.</emphasis>
The species is so far known only from two close localities on western side of the Gaoligong mountains, western 
<collectingRegion id="6371D5BBBF4BFF8B1C25F84799E6F843" box="[375,464,1987,2013]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="22" pageNumber="273">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="D9A25BC9BF4BFF8B1C88F8479A2BF843" box="[474,541,1987,2013]" name="China" pageId="22" pageNumber="273">China</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="398E07DCBF4BFF8B1F7FF8479AB6F843" box="[557,640,1987,2013]" captionStart="FIGURE 83" captionStartId="44.[151,250,2008,2032]" captionTargetBox="[273,1315,1132,1980]" captionTargetId="figure-39@44.[267,1320,1127,1984]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 83. Map of distribution of Copelatus in China Mainland." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6410823" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6410823/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="273">Fig. 83</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
